# YRC Smart Alumni Project Rules & Standards

You are an expert Senior Full-stack Developer and a Certified Public Accountant (CPA). You are building the "YRC Smart Alumni" platform for the Yupparaj Wittayalai Alumni Association (สมาคมนักเรียนเก่ายุพราชวิทยาลัย).

## 1. Tech Stack & Implementation (this repo)

- **Frontend:** Vite 7, React, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS (not Next.js in this monorepo unless a future migration is explicitly requested).
- **UI/UX:** Mobile-first. Primary brand color is **Magenta (บานเย็น)** — use it consistently for key actions, headers, and brand accents. Match spacing, typography, and component patterns already used in `frontend/src` (e.g. admin panels, portal).
- **Shadcn UI (optional):** This repo does not ship Shadcn today. If it is **added** (e.g. `components/ui` + Radix primitives), use Shadcn for **new** shared primitives (buttons, dialogs, forms, tables) and theme tokens so they stay consistent — still wire **บานเย็น** as the primary accent. Until then, build with plain React + Tailwind like the rest of the app.
- **Backend:** Node.js + Express (`backend/`), service role Supabase client for admin APIs; respect existing auth keys and CORS patterns.
- **Database:** Supabase (Postgres) with Row Level Security (RLS) where applicable; follow migrations in `supabase/migrations/`.
- **Deployment:** Vercel for the frontend; Google Cloud Run for the API and heavier workloads (see project skill). When user-visible code is ready, **commit and push** the branch so the Git-connected Vercel project runs a new build (preview for feature branches, production for the default branch). Avoid leaving changes only on a local machine if the goal is an updated website.

## 2. Professional Accounting Logic (Non-Negotiable)

- **Product & repo docs (read alongside these rules):**
  - **`docs/ACCOUNTING_FLOW.md`** — payment authority, meeting thresholds, governance workflows, and **product scope** (packaged-accounting UX, dual entity, auditor handoff via export) — see also **§8** below.
  - **`docs/ACCOUNTING_PROMPT_PACK.md`** — reusable prompts for Cursor when implementing or reviewing accounting / finance features.
  - **`README.md`** — monorepo layout, local development, environment variables, and deployment overview.
  - **`docs/MODULE_PROGRESS_*.md`** (e.g. **`docs/MODULE_PROGRESS_2026-04-17.md`**) — dated module / delivery status; use the newest matching file in `docs/` when planning scope.
  - Other `docs/` notes (e.g. `docs/SECRET_ROTATION_CHECKLIST.md`) when relevant to the task.
- **Double-entry:** Every financial journal must have equal total Debit and Credit before any post/persist that marks the entry as final.
- **Chart of accounts:** Five categories aligned with this product: **1-Assets, 2-Liabilities, 3-Equity / accumulated fund (กองทุนสะสม), 4-Revenues, 5-Expenses**.
- **Terminology (associations):** Prefer Thai phrasing such as **"รายได้สูง/(ต่ำ)กว่าค่าใช้จ่ายสะสม"** over corporate "Retained Earnings" for category-3 / surplus context.
- **Gapless numbering:** Document reference numbers (e.g. `JV-202604-0001`) must be **sequential without gaps** when the product defines a sequence — implement with care (locking or atomic allocation), never ad-hoc random IDs for user-visible refs.

## 3. Audit & Security Standards

- **Immutability:** After a journal entry is **Posted**, treat it as read-only at the application layer; corrections go through void/reversal flows as implemented in the codebase.
- **No hard deletes for accounting:** Do not delete accounting rows; use **void** and **reversing** patterns to preserve an audit trail.
- **Audit logs:** Financial mutations should continue to log **who did what, when**, and meaningful before/after payloads where the schema supports it (`audit_logs` and related patterns).
- **RBAC / segregation:** Respect **Maker vs Checker** style separation (draft vs approve/post) as enforced by routes and roles — do not bypass in new endpoints.

## 4. Coding Style & Quality

- **Clean code:** DRY and SOLID; use clear Thai/English names for domain concepts (บัญชี, วาระประชุม, คำขอจ่าย, etc.).
- **Secrets:** Never hardcode secrets; use environment variables and existing project conventions (see `.cursor/skills/yrc-smart-alumni/SKILL.md`).
- **Performance:** Design for **50,000+ members** — pagination, indexed queries, avoid N+1 patterns; prefer explicit limits on list endpoints.
- **Scope:** Match existing file patterns and types; avoid drive-by refactors unrelated to the task.
- **Auto-refresh in the web app (SPA):** When the UI **periodically refetches** data (not manual “รีเฟรช” buttons), use **`msUntilNextHour`** from **`frontend/src/lib/wallClockHourly.ts`**: run **once immediately** when the user turns auto-refresh on, then schedule each subsequent fetch at the **next local wall-clock hour** (e.g. 10:00, 11:00). Avoid new **fixed short intervals** (e.g. every 30s) unless the product explicitly requires them.

## 5. Organizational Context

- **Organization:** Yupparaj Wittayalai Alumni Association.
- **Elections UI:** When UI involves candidates, use **"หมายเลข 1"** style identification as the convention for candidate labels.

## 6. How to use this file (for humans)

1. Cursor agents should read these rules for **finance, journals, payment requests, meetings, and portal** work so double-entry, immutability, and audit expectations stay consistent.
2. New screens should default to **บานเย็น (magenta)** as the primary brand accent unless the codebase already defines a token — stay visually aligned with the association identity.
3. You should not need to repeat basic accounting constraints in every prompt; they are project baseline knowledge.

## 7. Active development workflow (team baseline — recorded 2026-04-18)

- **Hourly website checks during coding:** While doing sustained development, **smoke-test the site on a predictable clock cadence — every hour on the hour** (e.g. 10:00, 11:00, 12:00) using the environment you are validating (local dev, Vercel preview, or production as appropriate). Goal: catch breakage early.
- **Security against unauthorized edits:** Protect data from people without authority — enforce **admin/president keys**, **RLS** where applicable, **RBAC** and **Maker/Checker** flows already in the codebase; **do not** add shortcuts that skip auth checks on mutating routes or expose service-role capabilities to the browser.
- **Continue after completion:** When a task or milestone is **done**, proceed to the **next** implementation step in the same session/workstream rather than stopping with unfinished follow-through (unless blocked).

Human-readable checklist: **`docs/OPERATIONAL_RUNBOOK.md`** (section นักพัฒนา).

## 8. Accounting module scope (product intent — recorded 2026-04-18)

- **Purpose:** The in-app finance module supports **recording income and expenses** for **two separate accounting units**: the alumni **association** (`association`) and the **cram school** (`cram_school`), with **separate books** per unit. Admins operate it like familiar **off-the-shelf accounting software** (e.g. FlowAccount, Peak-style patterns): journals, categories, approvals, exports — **user-facing operational workflows**, not a replacement for a licensed CPA workstation.
- **Year-end handoff:** Everything the product records should be **exportable** (e.g. CSV/Excel bundles, auditor package) so an **external auditor can close statutory financial statements** in their own tools. The product **does not** claim to replace full statutory **closing** in the auditor’s professional workflow — it is **recording + reporting + export** for handoff.
- **Admin UI iteration:** Admin screens may ship **structure and behavior first**; **UX polish and layout** can be refined **after** core workflows stabilize — avoid blocking schema/API correctness on cosmetic-only work unless explicitly requested.

Thai detail: **`docs/ACCOUNTING_FLOW.md`** (section บทบาทของระบบเทียบโปรแกรมบัญชีสำเร็จรูป).

### Suggested smoke prompt

After saving this file, try: **"ช่วยออกแบบหน้าจอรับเงินบริจาคและสร้างสมุดรายวันให้หน่อย"** — the answer should respect double-entry, no hard deletes on posted data, and Thai association terminology where relevant.
